-- South Korean Stocks: Hyundai, LG Display, Samsung Electronics
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-01-27T06:49:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/south-korean-stocks-hyundai-lg-display-samsung-electronics.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  South Korea trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Seoul.  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  rose 0.4 percent to 1,964.83, the highest
close since Aug. 4 and the fifth day of advance. The benchmark
gained 0.8 percent this week.  Hyundai Motor Co. (005380)  (005380 KS) dropped 3.5 percent to
221,000 won, the most since Dec. 13. South Korea’s largest
automaker reported a 2 trillion won ($1.8 billion) net income in
the three months ended Dec. 31. The average of 13 analyst
estimates compiled by Bloomberg was for profit of 2.24 trillion
won.  Kia Motors Corp. (000270)  (000270 KS) retreated 2.8 percent to
67,100 won. The country’s second-largest carmaker reported
fourth quarter net income of 790.40 billion won, lower than
analysts’ estimate of 1.08 trillion won.  LG Display Co. (034220)  (034220 KS) gained 2 percent to 28,550 won.
The world’s second-largest maker of liquid-crystal displays
reported a fourth-quarter loss narrower than estimates, helped
by demand for panels used in 3-D televisions and mobile devices.
The company had a net loss of 6.3 billion won in the three
months ended in Dec. 31, compared with a loss of 268.4 billion
won a year ago, according to a regulatory filing. The average of
25 analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg was for a net loss of
83.9 billion won.  Samsung Electronics Co. (005930)  (005930 KS) advanced 1.1 percent to
1 million won, a record close.  Asia ’s largest consumer-
electronics company’s net income was 4 trillion won, compared
with 3.42 trillion won a year ago, the Suwon, South Korea-based
company said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
